  "text": "Our knowledge of the ecology of this species is limited to assumptions based on the situations where the dead animals have been found. We suspect the species may be associated with a wet bio-film community on active calcite formations in the cave. The species may be only seasonally active, and is apparently quite rare. The current long term drought in Southeast Arizona (about 12 years; [CITATION_1] ) may have impacted the population of this species, and could explain why we have not found live animals.",
